{% comment %}
  snippets/sponsored-ads.liquid
  [2] Dispatcher — routes a single in-feed ad block to its ad-unit renderer.

  Takes ONE block and renders it. Row-matching (which block(s) target
  row_index) and iteration over the full blocks array are NOT done here
  — see KNOWN ISSUE below, this currently doesn't match how
  collection-products.liquid calls this snippet.

  Parameters:
    block       {Object}  required — a section.blocks entry,
                           type "sponsored-products" or "sponsored-brands"
    collection  {Object}  optional — forwarded to sponsored-brands so it
                           can pull products from a merchant-picked
                           collection when source_mode == "collection"

  KNOWN ISSUE (pre-existing, not introduced by the product-card refactor):
    collection-products.liquid calls this snippet with
    `blocks: blocks, row_index: row_index` (plural blocks array + a row
    number), but this snippet's case statement only reads `block.type`
    (singular) — `blocks` and `row_index` are never referenced anywhere
    in this file. As written, this render call is a no-op: no ad block
    will ever appear in the grid until either (a) this snippet gains a
    loop that filters `blocks` by `block.settings.row == row_index` and
    renders each match, or (b) collection-products.liquid is changed to
    do that filtering itself and call this snippet once per matching
    block (singular), matching the parameter docs above.

  Children:
    snippets/sponsored-products.liquid
    snippets/sponsored-brands.liquid

  Asset ownership: this snippet loads no CSS/JS of its own.
    sponsored-ads.css and sponsored-ads.js are loaded once by
    collection-products.liquid (shared chrome — Sponsored label, card
    frame, rating row, CTA button — used by both children).
{% endcomment %}

{%- case block.type -%}

  {%- when 'sponsored-products' -%}
    {%- render 'sponsored-products', block: block -%}

  {%- when 'sponsored-brands' -%}
    {%- render 'sponsored-brands', block: block, collection: collection -%}

{%- endcase -%}
